{"title":"Storm Queen's shield","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Storm_Queen%27s_shield","type":"markdown","data":"***Version [0.30](/0.30 \"0.30\")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 \"0.32\") of Crawl.*\n\n|   |                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             |\n| - | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|   | A disc of crackling metal, created by a woman whose cunning artifice and crafty politics once united a continent. Most of her surviving inventions are closely guarded by various royals, ostensible proof of their claim to be her true successor, but this early prototype slipped through their fingers. |\n\n[![Storm Queen's shield.png](/images/9/97/Storm_Queen%27s_shield.png)](/File:Storm_Queen%27s_shield.png) ***the +5 Storm Queen's shield***\n\n+5 [kite shield](/Kite_shield \"Kite shield\")  \nWhen it blocks an attack, there's a 33% chance to electrocute the attacker (3d7 damage, ignoring 1/2 [AC](/AC \"AC\")).[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1)[\\[2\\]](#cite_note-2) This works up to 3 tiles away.  \n[rElec](/Electricity_resistance \"Electricity resistance\")  \nAllows [flight](/Flight \"Flight\")\n\n## Desirability\n\nThe **Storm Queen's shield**[\\[3\\]](#cite_note-3), as just a +5 kite shield of rElec, would already be a great find for many characters. The extra retaliation damage - which few monsters resist - only makes it better. A good item for any shield-using character, though some may prefer a highly enchanted [tower shield](/Tower_shield \"Tower shield\") instead.\n\n## History\n\n- The Storm Queen's shield was added in [0.30](/0.30 \"0.30\").\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [art-func.h:541](https://github.com/crawl/crawl/blob/0.30.1/crawl-ref/source/art-func.h#L541) (0.30.1)\n2. [↑](#cite_ref-2) [fineff.cc:511](https://github.com/crawl/crawl/blob/0.30.1/crawl-ref/source/fineff.cc#L511) (0.30.1)\n3. [↑](#cite_ref-3) [art-data.txt:1789](https://github.com/crawl/crawl/blob/0.30.1/crawl-ref/source/art-data.txt#L1789) (0.30.1)\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Storm Queen's shield - CrawlWiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Storm_Queen's_shield\",\"wgTitle\":\"Storm Queen's shield\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":72748,\"wgRevisionId\":72748,\"wgArticleId\":11097,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"0.30 articles\",\"Unrands\",\"Shields\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Storm_Queen's_shield\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":11097,\"wgRequestId\":\"4e1511f6994aef157be22477\",\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEdit