030}}\n{{flavour|A disc of crackling metal, created by a woman whose cunning artifice and crafty politics once united a continent. Most of her surviving inventions are closely guarded by various royals, ostensible proof of their claim to be her true successor, but this early prototype slipped through their fingers.}}\n\n[[File:Storm Queen's shield.png]] '''''the +5 Storm Queen's shield'''''\n\n+5 [[kite shield]]<br>\nWhen it blocks an attack, there's a 33% chance to electrocute the attacker (3d7 damage, ignoring 1/2 [[AC]]).<ref>{{source ref|0.30.1|art-func.h|541}}</ref><ref>{{source ref|0.30.1|fineff.cc|511}}</ref> This works up to 3 tiles away.<br>\n[[electricity resistance|rElec]]<br>\nAllows [[flight]]\n\n==Desirability==\nThe '''Storm Queen's shield'''<ref>{{source ref|0.30.1|art-data.txt|1789}}</ref>, as just a +5 kite shield of rElec, would already be a great find for many characters. The extra retaliation damage - which few monsters resist - only makes it better. A good item for any shield-using character, though some  may prefer a highly enchanted [[tower shield]] instead.\n\n==History==\n*The Storm Queen's shield was added in [[0.30]].\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n[[Category:Unrands]]\n[[Category:Shields]]"}